AUDIO: 'efficiency chart compared to other standard models, here\'s where it gets really interesting. The X-axis is the size, so the smaller the better, and then the Y-axis is performance, so the higher the better. Ideally, you want to'

[04:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'be in this upper left quadrant, and as you can see, this Bonsai family is over here. Way smaller, but just as performant as the other competitor models. And if you look at throughput, notice they\'re showing tokens per'

